In reality, exact matches such as the one above exist only for very few entities and predicates. More often than not the enumerations are incomplete and overlapping. For instance, an institute may use numberOfStaff or numberOfEmployees to mean the same thing and the corresponding enumerations could come from {{arxiv_2305_05403_FO0107||FO}} and {{arxiv_2305_05403_FO0108||FO}}.